      "text": "Officially there is no language called <i>Smalltalk</i>; there is a family of rather different languages called Smalltalk-<i>xx</i>, where the <i>xx</i> are the last two digits are the year that language was finalized. However most people just refer to Smalltalk as the language and mean the Smalltalk-80 dialect of the language (or a derivative of it as virtually all modern Smalltalk systems implement an evolution of Smalltalk-80).  Older dialects of Smalltalk include [[Smalltalk Seventy One]], [[Smalltalk Seventy Two]], and [[Smalltalk Seventy Eight]].  [[Self Language]] can be considered a newer dialect of Smalltalk.",
